Figure 
				1 visualizes the study design and major steps in development and assessment of the ensemble model. The ensemble model included two components: a baseline and a genetic model, where we compared multiple constructions of genetic models. We used cross validation to tune model parameters in the training dataset and evaluated the models in the independent test dataset. Models were trained using 70% of the available data from our multi-ethnic dataset and tested in the remaining 30%.

