In secondary analysis, we developed a new model that included local PRSs (Fig. 
					4a), constructed based on the UKBB + ICBP GWAS, with each local PRS being based on summary statistics restricted to an LD-region, with regions defined according to European populations. These PRSs used the clump & threshold methodology with p-value threshold < 10
					–2. Because gradient boosting trees models tend to overfit to the training dataset when many features are included, due to higher model complexity (see for instance the XGBoost tutorial
					https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html), we extended the development of the ensemble model to include a feature selection step using LASSO penalized regression, as described in Fig. 
					4a.

						Figure 4


