								a) The workflow of the ensemble model with the integration of the LASSO variable selection tool. To include local PRSs in the ensemble model while attempting to avoid overfitting, we added a LASSO selection step to the ensemble model development. As visualized, the residuals of the baseline model were used as the outcome in LASSO penalized regression with the local PRSs as features. LASSO substantially reduced the number of local PRSs (to 827 for SBP and 224 for DBP). The local PRSs selected by LASSO were then used as an input into the genetic model for prediction of the baseline residuals (





